{"title":"Troy Lee A3 enduro helmet is said to be so comfortable you’ll never take it off","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/03/18/troy-lee-a3-enduro-helmet-is-said-to-be-so-comfortable-youll-never-take-it-off/","date":1616040000000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>18The latest mountain bike helmet from Troy Lee Designs has landed in the form of the all-new open face A3. The brand emphasize this half-lid helmet is so comfortable that you’ll never take it off. But, the most interesting thing about the A3 is that independent helmet tester Virgina Tech awarded it their highest safety rating; 5 Stars. Here’s more.</p><h2>Troy Lee Designs A3 Helmet</h2><figure id=\"attachment_253174\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-253174\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121447/TROY-LEE-DESIGNS-A3-HELMET-IN-CAR.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121447/TROY-LEE-DESIGNS-A3-HELMET-IN-CAR.jpg\" alt=\"troy lee designs a3 mtb helmet rider wearing vehicle setting\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121447/TROY-LEE-DESIGNS-A3-HELMET-IN-CAR.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121447/TROY-LEE-DESIGNS-A3-HELMET-IN-CAR-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121447/TROY-LEE-DESIGNS-A3-HELMET-IN-CAR-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121447/TROY-LEE-DESIGNS-A3-HELMET-IN-CAR-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121447/TROY-LEE-DESIGNS-A3-HELMET-IN-CAR-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121447/TROY-LEE-DESIGNS-A3-HELMET-IN-CAR-696x464.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121447/TROY-LEE-DESIGNS-A3-HELMET-IN-CAR-1068x712.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121447/TROY-LEE-DESIGNS-A3-HELMET-IN-CAR-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-253174\">The Troy Lee A3 is certified to the following safety standards: CPSC 1203, CE EN 1078, AS NZ 2063:2008</figcaption></figure><p>The new Troy Lee A3 helmet, like the vast majority of high-end mountain bike helmets, gets a rotational impact protection system in the form of B-Series MIPS. Coverage from this 3-piece shell is fairly comprehensive as far as open face helmets go. An extended rear protects the back of your skull. We see it wraps around the sides slightly at the back, too.</p><figure id=\"attachment_253175\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-253175\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121609/tld-a3-mtb-helmet-black-red.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121609/tld-a3-mtb-helmet-black-red.jpg\" alt=\"tld a3 helmet black red mountain bike open face lid\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1007\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121609/tld-a3-mtb-helmet-black-red.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121609/tld-a3-mtb-helmet-black-red-297x249.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121609/tld-a3-mtb-helmet-black-red-800x671.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121609/tld-a3-mtb-helmet-black-red-120x101.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121609/tld-a3-mtb-helmet-black-red-768x644.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121609/tld-a3-mtb-helmet-black-red-696x584.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121609/tld-a3-mtb-helmet-black-red-1068x896.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121609/tld-a3-mtb-helmet-black-red-500x420.jpg 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-253175\">Those visor screws are composite smart shear screws, made to shear away during severe impact or a direct hit to the visor</figcaption></figure><p>The A3 gets the same high and low-speed impact energy absorption tech we see on the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2017/03/06/troy-lee-designs-a2-helmet-blends-mips-tld-trail-styling/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Troy Lee A2</a>; that’s EPP and EPS co-molded. At $220, the A3 is the significantly more expensive option, even though the A2 was also awarded 5 Stars from <a href=\"https://helmet.beam.vt.edu/bicycle-helmet-ratings.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Virginia Tech</a>. So, if it’s just as safe, what else are you getting for your money?</p><h3>Troy Lee Proprietary Sweat Management</h3><figure id=\"attachment_253173\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-253173\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121232/troy-lee-a3-helmet-sweat-glide-management.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121232/troy-lee-a3-helmet-sweat-glide-management.jpg\" alt=\"troy lee designs a3 mtb helmet spa scenario sweat glide system\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121232/troy-lee-a3-helmet-sweat-glide-management.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121232/troy-lee-a3-helmet-sweat-glide-management-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121232/troy-lee-a3-helmet-sweat-glide-management-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121232/troy-lee-a3-helmet-sweat-glide-management-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121232/troy-lee-a3-helmet-sweat-glide-management-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121232/troy-lee-a3-helmet-sweat-glide-management-696x464.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121232/troy-lee-a3-helmet-sweat-glide-management-1068x712.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17121232/troy-lee-a3-helmet-sweat-glide-management-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-253173\">The Sweat Glide System may prove to be useful for riders who find their goggles steam up too easily</figcaption></figure><p>The Troy Lee A3 is their first mountain bike helmet to feature the Sweat Glide system, said to direct sweat away from the rider’s eyes and googles or sunglasses. This is EVA sweat-wicking foam that sits behind the comfort liner located at the forehead region. It is replaceable, with spares are supplied in the box.</p><h3>What else?</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123429/TLD-a3-white-red-colorway-fidlock-closure.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123429/TLD-a3-white-red-colorway-fidlock-closure.jpg\" alt=\"troy lee designs a3 mountain bike helmet white\" width=\"1200\" height=\"966\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123429/TLD-a3-white-red-colorway-fidlock-closure.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123429/TLD-a3-white-red-colorway-fidlock-closure-297x239.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123429/TLD-a3-white-red-colorway-fidlock-closure-800x644.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123429/TLD-a3-white-red-colorway-fidlock-closure-120x97.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123429/TLD-a3-white-red-colorway-fidlock-closure-768x618.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123429/TLD-a3-white-red-colorway-fidlock-closure-696x560.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123429/TLD-a3-white-red-colorway-fidlock-closure-1068x860.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123429/TLD-a3-white-red-colorway-fidlock-closure-522x420.jpg 522w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\"></a></p><p>Troy Lee have partnered with FIDLOCK to create a custom magnetic chin strap closure. It allows one-hand fastening and, on all the FIDLOCK-rocking helmets I’ve tested, is a durable mechanism. That replaces the standard plastic buckle seen on the A2 and other Troy Lee open face helmets.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123645/TLD_B21S_A3_UNO_SILELE_01.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123645/TLD_B21S_A3_UNO_SILELE_01.jpg\" alt=\"troy lee designs a3 silver\" width=\"1200\" height=\"995\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123645/TLD_B21S_A3_UNO_SILELE_01.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123645/TLD_B21S_A3_UNO_SILELE_01-297x246.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123645/TLD_B21S_A3_UNO_SILELE_01-800x663.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123645/TLD_B21S_A3_UNO_SILELE_01-120x100.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123645/TLD_B21S_A3_UNO_SILELE_01-768x637.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123645/TLD_B21S_A3_UNO_SILELE_01-696x577.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123645/TLD_B21S_A3_UNO_SILELE_01-1068x886.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123645/TLD_B21S_A3_UNO_SILELE_01-507x420.jpg 507w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\"></a></p><p>The 3-Way Magnajust visor is said to move up sufficiently to allow the stowage of googles underneath. No fewer than 16 vents channel air over your head to keep you cool on hot summer’s day climbs.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123847/troy-lee-designs-a3-mtb-helmet-top-view-16-vents.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123847/troy-lee-designs-a3-mtb-helmet-top-view-16-vents.jpg\" alt=\"troy lee designs a3 mtb helemt top view\" width=\"1200\" height=\"565\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123847/troy-lee-designs-a3-mtb-helmet-top-view-16-vents.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123847/troy-lee-designs-a3-mtb-helmet-top-view-16-vents-297x140.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123847/troy-lee-designs-a3-mtb-helmet-top-view-16-vents-800x377.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123847/troy-lee-designs-a3-mtb-helmet-top-view-16-vents-120x57.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123847/troy-lee-designs-a3-mtb-helmet-top-view-16-vents-768x362.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123847/troy-lee-designs-a3-mtb-helmet-top-view-16-vents-696x328.jpg 696w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123847/troy-lee-designs-a3-mtb-helmet-top-view-16-vents-1068x503.jpg 1068w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/17123847/troy-lee-designs-a3-mtb-helmet-top-view-16-vents-892x420.jpg 892w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\"></a></p><p>In addition to the Sweat Glide spares, Troy Lee provide a spare comfort liner (anti-microbial treated), two spare visor screws, a sticker kit and a helmet carrying bag.&nbsp;</p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>The all-new Troy Lee A3 helmet retails at $220 and is available in sizes XS-XXL, covering head circumferences from 53cm to 63cm.</p><p><a href=\"https://troyleedesigns.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>TroyLeeDesigns.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"d22baf5e160473b11e48d039c2839738cb4156209d2475f93437688e0baa247d","category":"Cycling"}